<br>
Personally I think Verant screwed up this whole epic implementation. For any class there shouldn't be more than a handfull of epics per server.  I have completed 3 epics so far and have a druid epic, monk epic and cleric epic. There is NO way I should have been able to accomplish this.<br>
<br>
Pre patch the Mage, Necro, Wizard, Warrior and Druid epics were the only ones I felt rare enough to be called &quot;epic.&quot;  When you saw somebody with one of these, you knew you were looking at one of the few on the server. That person had the conections, resources, patience and determination to get it accomplished. And yes there is an element of luck or being in the right place at the right time that plays a factor.<br>
<br>
Yes you pay the same 10 bucks everybody else does. Yes you have every right to start the quest if you choose. But if some of the components take too much time, or you have too many real life commitments to devote to the game, then perhaps this particular item isn't for you.  There are plenty of items that I would like to get but I probably never will.  These items are not for me. Why does everybody have this sense of entitlement to the epics? Just because you can start a quest entitles you to finish it? How many people started the Tunarean Court Membership quest only to get stuck because they cannot get to PoM?  Until you have the resources to get there and kill Lith, this item is not for you.<br>
<br>
When I saw the descriptions of the epic quests before they went live, I didn't expect to get one myself. I figured they would be like GM quests where the reward would be so rare that only a few would have one on each server.  With the stats on these epics I highly doubt there will ever be a better item to replace this slot.  This entire quest can now be done front to back with 1-2 people and a couple fights taking 1-2 groups.  Epic quests in general have become the biggest example of imbalanced risk vs. reward since I looted a Dragon Spine Staff off of Silverwing.<br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that any changes to the epics should have made them as rare as the Mage/Necro epics, not this free-for-all that we have now.<br>
<br>
