</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/21/01 4:31:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.freshpope.com/gfx/ctree2sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on the epic changes.</span><hr size=1> The fault doesn't lie with players who feel entitled to their epics.  The fault lies with Verant for the huge disparity in the difficulty of these quests.  Rogue/Shaman/Cleric/Monk/Ranger epics are practically standard equipment now, and to me that is just ridiculous. There should have been much more consultation between the different quest designers to get some kind of consistency.  <br>
<br>
We all know that not everyone should get an epic.  However, I also feel that everyone should have the same chance at an epic and the two are not mutually exclusive.  Regarding something like this, it's ludicrous to reward people for making arbitrary decisions (i.e. which class you picked to level).  When you see someone else getting something better than what you have and having a much much easier time of it because of that arbitrary decision there is bound to be jealousy.  And given the nature of the way the internet and EQ works that jealousy turns into whining and flames on message boards.  It's really a no-win situation.  They couldn't make the easy quests hard, and they couldn't make the hard quests too much easier.  <br>
<br>
