Personally I think that they should be available to whoever is able to do the quest. This is a game for crying out loud. Who cares if more than a handful of druids have their Epic weapon? If you do care, why do you care? I bet the reasons are purely selfish ones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulanimretnpajamas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lanimret Npajamas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/22/01 8:35:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My thoughts on the epic changes.</span><hr size=1> You have to remember, if Verant made epics that rare, no one worthwild would complete them. All the work Verant put into the weapons would be for not, and people would complain, as they should, &quot;You are always catering to the uber crowd!&quot;. The put something in the game to give us, the not quite uber, something to play for. Honestly, if they put my quest in VP like you are suggesting, I would quit the game. My only motivation at this point, after 2 years of playing, is to get my epic. I think all epics should be right around the level of the druid epic in difficulty. I think upping Faydedar a bit in level would be appropriate (maybe 57-58), and having the remains spawn randomly over a certain time period would also save a lot of heartache. Other then that, it's perfect how it is and gives us all something to work towards. Something that seems nearly impossible for many of us, but just barely in reach if we try hard enough. Now if you are in an Uber guild, its a different story all together, but honestly I am sick of hearing the uber guilded bitching, you have it easy.<br>
